==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Egyptian
<hw>E*gyp"tian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Aegyptius</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ (L. <ets>Aegyptus</ets>) Egypt:
cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧gyptien</ets>. Cf. <er>Gypsy</er>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to Egypt, in Africa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Egyptian bean</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<cd>The beanlike fruit of an aquatic plant (<spn>Nelumbium
speciosum</spn>), somewhat resembling the water lily.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd>
<cd>See under <er>Bean</er>, 1.</cd> -- <col><b>Egyptian
cross</b></col>. <cd>See <xex>Illust.</xex> (No. 6) of
<er>Cross</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Egyptian thorn</b></col>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a medium-sized tree (<spn>Acacia vera</spn>). It
is one of the chief sources of the best gum arabic.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Egyptian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Egyptian
<hw>E*gyp"tian</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native, or one of
the people, of Egypt; also, the Egyptian language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gypsy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Egyptize</ent>⟦br⟧
